Let's go

518
00:37:45,596 --> 00:37:47,431
and get ready for the evening roll-call.

519
00:37:48,391 --> 00:37:51,269
Why don't you go ahead first?
I need to stop by somewhere.

520
00:37:51,352 --> 00:37:52,228
Where?

521
00:37:56,941 --> 00:37:57,942
Yes.

522
00:37:59,277 --> 00:38:02,989
It'll take me about ten minutes,
so please wait for me.

523
00:38:04,073 --> 00:38:08,703
DO NOT ENTER

524
00:38:11,956 --> 00:38:13,749
KIM DON-GUN,
SOUTH CHUNGCHEONG 90J 1398

525
00:38:13,833 --> 00:38:15,167
All right.

526
00:38:17,253 --> 00:38:20,256
-Professor Yu, I have something to…
-Later.

527
00:38:28,389 --> 00:38:30,182
What are you doing?

528
00:38:30,266 --> 00:38:32,935
I need to ask you now, not later.

529
00:38:33,019 --> 00:38:34,645
Get out! Get off now!

530
00:38:34,729 --> 00:38:36,856
I said I have something to ask you!

531
00:38:36,939 --> 00:38:38,899
Darn it. I'm not responsible for this.

532
00:38:41,235 --> 00:38:42,278
Professor Yu.

533
00:38:43,529 --> 00:38:47,116
I heard you met
all the truck drivers within a week.

534
00:38:47,199 --> 00:38:48,242
Yes.

535
00:38:52,038 --> 00:38:56,667
This is where they park their trucks,
so you must've met a lot of them.

536
00:38:56,751 --> 00:38:59,587
I can't believe
you actually met all of them.

537
00:38:59,670 --> 00:39:02,089
-Here you go.
-Thank you.

538
00:39:02,173 --> 00:39:04,383
I'll check as soon as I can
and return it to you.

539
00:39:04,467 --> 00:39:06,886
It rained a lot that night,

540
00:39:06,969 --> 00:39:08,971
so I'm not sure
what got caught on my dashcam.

541
00:39:09,764 --> 00:39:15,311
Goodness. The road there isn't paved,
so it was all muddy.

542
00:39:15,394 --> 00:39:18,314
When it rains, the truck gets messy.

543
00:39:30,409 --> 00:39:31,952
What are you doing?

544
00:39:38,501 --> 00:39:42,129
It's 8:57:14 p.m.

545
00:39:50,888 --> 00:39:55,768
It's 8:57:34 p.m.

546
00:39:56,352 --> 00:39:58,020
It's a gray sedan.

547
00:39:58,104 --> 00:40:01,148
What's the number? Four, seven…

548
00:40:02,566 --> 00:40:03,609
What's the last one?

549
00:40:03,692 --> 00:40:06,362
Isn't that 4, 1?

550
00:40:06,445 --> 00:40:07,446
What?

551
00:40:13,411 --> 00:40:14,453
Hey, it's me.

552
00:40:14,537 --> 00:40:17,456
I'll send you a file,
so can you analyze the video

553
00:40:17,540 --> 00:40:20,167
and get me the car model
and its plate number?

554
00:40:24,130 --> 00:40:25,548
Where are we going again?

555
00:40:27,550 --> 00:40:28,759
Aren't we going back to school?

556
00:40:35,975 --> 00:40:37,726
Where did he go?

557
00:40:39,353 --> 00:40:41,730
It's almost time
for the evening roll-call.

558
00:40:44,900 --> 00:40:46,402
What's all this?

559
00:40:47,695 --> 00:40:48,529
KANG SUN-HO

560
00:40:48,612 --> 00:40:50,197
ACCORDING TO THE CONSTITUTION…

561
00:40:51,949 --> 00:40:53,451
THE MIRANDA RULE!

562
00:40:53,534 --> 00:40:54,952
"Miranda"?

563
00:40:56,996 --> 00:40:59,540
Don't you know
that I'll get a penalty for AWOL?

564
00:40:59,623 --> 00:41:02,918
So why did you have to follow me?
I'm so busy.

565
00:41:04,503 --> 00:41:06,672
PROVINCIAL POLICE AGENCY

566
00:41:06,755 --> 00:41:09,550
-Are we going to a police station now?
-Yes.

567
00:41:10,134 --> 00:41:11,343
Why?

568
00:41:11,427 --> 00:41:13,929
I smell something fishy.

569
00:41:14,638 --> 00:41:17,224
I smell something fishy.

570
00:41:25,858 --> 00:41:29,195
If you want to go up, just go.
Why are you waiting here?

571
00:41:29,278 --> 00:41:30,654
Be quiet.

572
00:41:30,738 --> 00:41:34,074
Hey, Detective Lee.
You gained some weight.

573
00:41:34,158 --> 00:41:36,327
I guess you're only working from the desk.

574
00:41:36,410 --> 00:41:38,454
-Gosh.
-Let's go.

575
00:41:39,163 --> 00:41:40,498
Hey, Detective Kim.

576
00:41:40,581 --> 00:41:42,875
I saw that you changed your car.

577
00:41:42,958 --> 00:41:44,793
Don't get any bribes.

578
00:41:44,877 --> 00:41:45,920
I'm watching you.

579
00:41:46,003 --> 00:41:48,005
I bought it
on a five-year installment plan.

580
00:41:48,088 --> 00:41:49,340
Don't shoot your mouth off.

581
00:41:49,423 --> 00:41:52,426
I was just kidding. See you.

582
00:41:56,972 --> 00:41:57,848
Hello, sir.

583
00:41:59,683 --> 00:42:02,019
Hey, Senior Inspector Yu.

584
00:42:02,853 --> 00:42:06,482
I heard you were going to appoint me
somewhere else again.

585
00:42:06,565 --> 00:42:07,900
Thank you.

586
00:42:08,484 --> 00:42:12,321
But Captain Choi isn't
the type to do that.

587
00:42:12,905 --> 00:42:14,281
Right.

588
00:42:15,866 --> 00:42:18,827
It's not Captain Choi who asked me.

589
00:42:18,911 --> 00:42:21,121
I thought it'd be a waste to let you go.

590
00:42:21,205 --> 00:42:23,791
I didn't want a competent officer like you
to be stuck at school.

591
00:42:25,000 --> 00:42:26,794
I see.

592
00:42:26,877 --> 00:42:28,337
Anyway, what are you doing here?

593
00:42:29,255 --> 00:42:32,216
My colleague got hurt,
so I came to pick up his stuff.

594
00:42:33,425 --> 00:42:35,928
You mean Inspector Park Cheol-jin?

595
00:42:37,179 --> 00:42:39,223
-Yes.
-I see.

596
00:42:39,306 --> 00:42:41,016
They got the real culprit.

597
00:42:43,435 --> 00:42:44,937
They're investigating him now.

598
00:42:45,604 --> 00:42:46,564
They caught him?

599
00:42:50,776 --> 00:42:52,528
Oh, right.

600
00:42:52,611 --> 00:42:56,490
I mixed it up
with the Seongsu-dong theft case.

601
00:42:58,867 --> 00:43:01,704
Gosh, how could you mix that up?

602
00:43:01,787 --> 00:43:04,123
I know, right? Good night, then.

603
00:43:04,206 --> 00:43:05,708
-Okay. See you.
-Bye.

604
00:43:08,752 --> 00:43:11,005
-Hey, let's get going.
-Sorry?

605
00:43:15,551 --> 00:43:17,177
Chief Han.

606
00:43:19,305 --> 00:43:22,308
What's this about? Why are we here?

607
00:43:23,058 --> 00:43:24,518
Didn't you see him earlier?

608
00:43:25,144 --> 00:43:27,354
His face when I told him
that the real culprit was caught.

609
00:43:27,438 --> 00:43:29,023
I can tell who's guilty.

610
00:43:29,106 --> 00:43:31,984
They can't hide their feelings
in that instant.

611
00:43:33,402 --> 00:43:35,654
But I only got circumstantial proof.

612
00:43:35,738 --> 00:43:37,197
I have no evidence.

613
00:43:37,781 --> 00:43:39,783
-Gosh.
-What are you going to do?

614
00:43:40,659 --> 00:43:43,537
Well, we'll have to wait
until Cheol-jin wakes up.

615
00:43:43,621 --> 00:43:45,122
Darn it.

616
00:43:45,205 --> 00:43:48,375
What did you want to ask me?

617
00:43:48,459 --> 00:43:52,129
I'll ask you later.

618
00:43:53,047 --> 00:43:55,674
Is Cheol-jin okay though?

619
00:44:05,976 --> 00:44:09,480
I was really desperate when I had to
get the money for my dad's hospital fees.

620
00:44:16,779 --> 00:44:18,947
It looks like Professor Yu
is desperate too.

621
00:44:20,157 --> 00:44:21,992
So please wake up soon.

622
00:44:38,175 --> 00:44:39,009
Right.

623
00:44:39,093 --> 00:44:42,137
You said you wanted to ask me something.

624
00:44:42,221 --> 00:44:45,933
-Are you not going to ask me?
-I think I heard my answer.

625
00:44:46,016 --> 00:44:47,309
What?

626
00:44:59,905 --> 00:45:00,739
Professor Yu.

627
00:45:01,573 --> 00:45:04,868
Why did you help the drunk man
in the emergency center?

628
00:45:04,952 --> 00:45:06,120
What do you mean?

629
00:45:06,703 --> 00:45:09,206
"We need to protect criminals.
They have rights too."

630
00:45:09,289 --> 00:45:11,125
Is that what you believe in?

631
00:45:12,084 --> 00:45:15,379
Beliefs aren't important.
I just follow my instincts.

632
00:45:15,462 --> 00:45:18,298
Why make it so complicated
and question everything?

633
00:45:18,382 --> 00:45:20,801
I don't have such beliefs. It's simple.

634
00:45:20,884 --> 00:45:23,303
"Protect them and catch them." Okay?

635
00:45:23,387 --> 00:45:25,889
If you want to do that,
you'll need to work out.

636
00:45:25,973 --> 00:45:29,184
How can a weak man like you
protect or catch anyone?

637
00:45:49,204 --> 00:45:51,790
Guys, do you want to win
that girl's heart?

638
00:45:52,791 --> 00:45:54,251
-Of course!
-Of course!

639
00:45:54,334 --> 00:45:56,003
-Here I go!
-Bring it on!

640
00:46:04,595 --> 00:46:05,762
LEAVE YOUR JUDO CLUB APPLICATION HERE

641
00:46:05,846 --> 00:46:07,139
This isn't the time for skincare.

642
00:46:07,222 --> 00:46:08,640
We haven't received a single application!

643
00:46:08,724 --> 00:46:10,267
NEW MEMBERS WANTED

644
00:46:10,350 --> 00:46:11,935
Just wait until you get to my age.

645
00:46:12,019 --> 00:46:14,271
Freckles scare me
more than zero applications.

646
00:46:15,022 --> 00:46:17,524
You can't see them now,
but they'll be visible later on.

647
00:46:18,650 --> 00:46:22,279
You tricked me when I was a freshman
and now I have to put up with this.

648
00:46:22,362 --> 00:46:24,615
What do you mean, I tricked you?

649
00:46:26,241 --> 00:46:29,745
You said this would be the highlight
of my campus life. Where are the boys?

650
00:46:29,828 --> 00:46:31,288
I hate you!

651
00:46:31,371 --> 00:46:33,707
What if they decide
to get rid of the club?

652
00:46:33,790 --> 00:46:35,042
This is driving me nuts.

653
00:46:42,299 --> 00:46:44,468
We'd like to join the judo club.

654
00:46:47,513 --> 00:46:48,472
Here come the boys.

655
00:46:53,268 --> 00:46:54,102
Welcome.

656
00:46:54,186 --> 00:46:57,481
I'll teach you how to do a breakfall
to see if you're qualified.

657
00:46:57,564 --> 00:46:58,899
Wait, there's a test?

658
00:46:59,900 --> 00:47:02,486
Here I come!

659
00:47:08,867 --> 00:47:12,246
Now that you've joined the judo club
and will be learning from me,

660
00:47:12,829 --> 00:47:15,332
you'll become the toughest cookies
in the entire school!

661
00:47:18,502 --> 00:47:21,088
Maybe it'd be easier to just drop dead.

662
00:47:21,713 --> 00:47:23,006
Then she's mine.

663
00:47:24,091 --> 00:47:24,967
Professor.

664
00:47:25,467 --> 00:47:27,594
I want to try one more time. Let's go!

665
00:47:32,140 --> 00:47:34,059
-I'm sorry.
-He doesn't know it yet,

666
00:47:34,142 --> 00:47:35,435
but I joined the relations team too.

667
00:47:36,019 --> 00:47:38,605
-All right!
-Eon-ju is a member of that club.

668
00:47:40,148 --> 00:47:42,526
I can handle two clubs.

669
00:47:42,609 --> 00:47:45,153
-No! I will try one more time. I'm okay!
-I won.

670
00:47:45,237 --> 00:47:47,447
Beom-tae can't beat me.

671
00:47:48,740 --> 00:47:49,866
Look at that!

672
00:47:52,494 --> 00:47:54,288
-My goodness.
-I'm okay.

673
00:47:54,871 --> 00:47:56,039
-Right.
-It hurts.

674
00:47:56,123 --> 00:47:58,542
-I sent you those photos.
-No, I want to try again.

675
00:47:58,625 --> 00:47:59,793
I'm okay!

676
00:48:01,044 --> 00:48:02,671
Joon-wuk.

677
00:48:02,754 --> 00:48:04,798
You call yourself Mr. Popular.

678
00:48:04,881 --> 00:48:06,675
Everyone would agree.

679
00:48:06,758 --> 00:48:08,677
-Right, sure.
-That's right.

680
00:48:08,760 --> 00:48:10,053
Can you send me the photos

681
00:48:10,137 --> 00:48:12,598
of those who tagged
"Korean National Police University"

682
00:48:12,681 --> 00:48:14,016
on Monday night?

683
00:48:14,891 --> 00:48:16,727
-Okay.
-Thanks.

684
00:48:16,810 --> 00:48:17,978
No problem.

685
00:48:18,061 --> 00:48:19,521
KIM BA-DA,
KOREAN NATIONAL POLICE UNIVERSITY

686
00:48:19,605 --> 00:48:22,024
It was posted on Monday at 9:30 p.m.

687
00:48:22,774 --> 00:48:24,484
And the person who posted it
used the Wi-Fi

688
00:48:25,110 --> 00:48:26,320
in the lobby at the dorm.

689
00:48:28,989 --> 00:48:30,490
What?

690
00:48:48,759 --> 00:48:50,719
Hey, did you hear?

691
00:48:53,138 --> 00:48:57,100
They caught the person
who posted the video of Kang-hui's mother.

692
00:48:57,184 --> 00:48:58,852
What?

693
00:49:06,652 --> 00:49:07,903
So it was you.

694
00:49:16,828 --> 00:49:18,580
What a nasty girl you are.

695
00:49:19,373 --> 00:49:20,624
Everyone!

696
00:49:21,625 --> 00:49:24,628
My daughter tells me
she wants to die before me.

697
00:49:29,883 --> 00:49:31,301
Why did you do that?

698
00:49:31,385 --> 00:49:33,553
Darn it.

699
00:49:34,388 --> 00:49:36,848
Then I'll go show this to Ms. Baek.

700
00:49:38,308 --> 00:49:40,227
I did it to join the student council.

701
00:49:42,187 --> 00:49:43,397
Darn it.

702
00:49:44,481 --> 00:49:46,400
There are only two spots left.

703
00:49:46,483 --> 00:49:49,611
But they look at your grades,
so I can only join if she gives up.

704
00:49:49,695 --> 00:49:51,363
You did that for something so petty?

705
00:49:51,446 --> 00:49:53,782
"Petty"? Don't you know
that the council members

706
00:49:53,865 --> 00:49:55,575
have it easy after joining the force?

707
00:49:55,659 --> 00:49:58,161
If you want to "have it easy"
as a police officer,

708
00:49:58,245 --> 00:50:00,330
you should just quit now, you idiot.

709
00:50:01,540 --> 00:50:03,500
You're not going to tell anyone, right?

710
00:50:03,583 --> 00:50:06,878
Go to the student council's office
and withdraw your application.

711
00:50:07,379 --> 00:50:08,338
-Jeez.
-If you don't,

712
00:50:08,422 --> 00:50:10,215
I'll make you too embarrassed
to stay in school.

713
00:50:11,925 --> 00:50:12,884
Hold on.

714
00:50:14,010 --> 00:50:15,595
How did you know it was me?

715
00:50:18,348 --> 00:50:19,766
That look on your face.

716
00:50:20,767 --> 00:50:22,269
I can tell who's guilty.

717
00:50:22,352 --> 00:50:24,771
They can't hide
their feelings in that instant.

718
00:50:35,407 --> 00:50:37,367
Oh Kang-hui's grades are much better,

719
00:50:37,451 --> 00:50:39,661
but with all those talks about her,
we shouldn't let her in.

720
00:50:39,745 --> 00:50:40,996
Totally.

721
00:50:41,079 --> 00:50:43,081
She'll destroy the council's reputation.

722
00:50:43,165 --> 00:50:46,501
We absolutely cannot accept her.
There's no way…

723
00:50:46,585 --> 00:50:47,627
She's here.

724
00:50:48,545 --> 00:50:49,880
I'd like my application back.

725
00:50:49,963 --> 00:50:51,173
Okay, here.

726
00:50:51,256 --> 00:50:52,716
Wait.

727
00:50:52,799 --> 00:50:53,925
Why?

728
00:50:54,426 --> 00:50:56,261
I've decided to withdraw my application,

729
00:50:56,803 --> 00:51:00,640
so you can't disqualify me
for such unfair, ridiculous reasons.

730
00:51:01,391 --> 00:51:02,809
Can I have my application back?

731
00:51:04,478 --> 00:51:05,645
Here.

732
00:51:11,985 --> 00:51:12,986
PROFESSOR YU DONG-MAN

733
00:51:15,155 --> 00:51:16,990
HERE'S THE VIDEO ANALYSIS RESULT

734
00:51:18,408 --> 00:51:20,827
HERE'S THE VIDEO ANALYSIS RESULT

735
00:51:27,209 --> 00:51:28,376
Hello?

736
00:51:29,127 --> 00:51:31,505
What? He's awake?

737
00:51:32,964 --> 00:51:34,257
How is he?

738
00:51:37,594 --> 00:51:38,720
PARKING FOR PROFESSORS ONLY

739
00:51:54,611 --> 00:51:55,821
I heard you joined the judo club.

740
00:51:56,738 --> 00:51:59,032
Yes, I want to build strength.

741
00:51:59,950 --> 00:52:03,036
Did you get into the student council?

742
00:52:03,119 --> 00:52:05,872
No, I applied to join the relations team.

743
00:52:05,956 --> 00:52:09,042
I'm a total newsmaker. Who else
would join the relations team if I don't?

744
00:52:10,544 --> 00:52:13,421
So many freshmen will apply next year
if you do the promotion.

745
00:52:13,505 --> 00:52:15,924
I'll make sure
it's more competitive than ever.

746
00:52:20,095 --> 00:52:22,264
It's Professor Kwon's class.

747
00:52:25,725 --> 00:52:27,811
That's it for today's class.

748
00:52:32,524 --> 00:52:33,567
May I

749
00:52:35,235 --> 00:52:38,405
answer the question you asked me
last time?

750
00:52:41,658 --> 00:52:44,494
The answer had better
be worthy of my time.

751
00:52:54,379 --> 00:52:57,007
I stumbled upon a book in the library.

752
00:52:57,090 --> 00:52:59,676
It was a book about Miranda

753
00:53:00,427 --> 00:53:01,845
of the well-known Miranda rule.

754
00:53:04,848 --> 00:53:07,434
Ernesto Miranda was a serial rapist.

755
00:53:08,351 --> 00:53:11,187
He confessed to his rape charges
during a police interrogation,

756
00:53:11,271 --> 00:53:13,023
but the court
ruled his confession inadmissible

757
00:53:13,106 --> 00:53:15,984
because he had not been informed
of his rights to remain silent

758
00:53:16,067 --> 00:53:19,988
and to consult with an attorney,
so he ended up being released on parole.

759
00:53:22,198 --> 00:53:26,202
Ultimately, this verdict set an example
that justice can only be truly realized

760
00:53:26,286 --> 00:53:27,704
through lawful means.

761
00:53:27,787 --> 00:53:30,165
However, there are still
many controversies

762
00:53:30,248 --> 00:53:31,541
surrounding this decision.

763
00:53:33,919 --> 00:53:37,339
Personally,
I don't agree with the verdict.

764
00:53:37,422 --> 00:53:39,090
The rights of someone who kidnapped

765
00:53:39,174 --> 00:53:41,885
and raped an 18-year-old girl
are not important.

766
00:53:44,930 --> 00:53:49,392
But perhaps by following the rules
and accepting everyone's rights,

767
00:53:51,102 --> 00:53:52,979
we can protect those

768
00:53:54,606 --> 00:53:57,067
who truly need to be
protected from such criminals.

769
00:53:58,860 --> 00:54:00,946
So my answer to your question

770
00:54:01,655 --> 00:54:03,239
remains the same.

771
00:54:03,990 --> 00:54:05,241
Be it an innocent civilian

772
00:54:06,242 --> 00:54:07,327
or a criminal.

773
00:54:07,911 --> 00:54:09,454
I believe everyone should be protected,

774
00:54:10,205 --> 00:54:11,998
within the frame of laws

775
00:54:12,916 --> 00:54:14,084
and rules we must follow.

776
00:54:15,085 --> 00:54:16,753
Because we're members of the police

777
00:54:18,296 --> 00:54:20,090
and a law enforcement agency.

778
00:54:49,869 --> 00:54:53,581
The verdict wasn't made
to protect Miranda.

779
00:54:54,165 --> 00:54:56,584
The officer who caused an accident
and led the criminal to die

780
00:54:56,668 --> 00:54:59,963
didn't get dismissed and punished
because the criminal was innocent.

781
00:55:01,172 --> 00:55:02,757
We shouldn't let our emotions
do the judging.

782
00:55:02,841 --> 00:55:04,843
We should leave it to the law.

783
00:55:06,594 --> 00:55:08,805
Understanding the world through the law

784
00:55:09,848 --> 00:55:12,726
is the legal mind you must learn

785
00:55:12,809 --> 00:55:16,104
in the first class
of the Constitutional Law course.

786
00:55:17,814 --> 00:55:18,857
Kang Sun-ho.

787
00:55:21,026 --> 00:55:22,152
Well done.

788
00:55:46,718 --> 00:55:48,511
Good job, Sun-ho.

789
00:56:04,319 --> 00:56:07,072
I didn't know bananas were this good.

790
00:56:07,155 --> 00:56:08,281
My gosh.

791
00:56:15,330 --> 00:56:16,539
Cheol-jin!

792
00:56:16,623 --> 00:56:19,667
Hey, my head! I can't breathe!

793
00:56:19,751 --> 00:56:22,712
Hey! Are you okay?

794
00:56:22,796 --> 00:56:24,631
You punk. You made me worry.

795
00:56:25,215 --> 00:56:27,342
Why didn't you worry about me
when this didn't happen?

796
00:56:29,761 --> 00:56:31,971
Look at him. He's back.

797
00:56:32,055 --> 00:56:33,890
-He's back, Captain.
-Dong-man.

798
00:56:33,973 --> 00:56:35,183
Right.

799
00:56:35,266 --> 00:56:37,560
You remember the jerks
who did this to you, right?

800
00:56:39,479 --> 00:56:40,563
What?

801
00:56:41,231 --> 00:56:44,400
-Dong-man.
-it must've been a big shock.

802
00:56:44,484 --> 00:56:47,153
Then do you remember
the phone call we had?

803
00:56:47,737 --> 00:56:50,323
You said it has something
to do with the Police University.

804
00:56:52,450 --> 00:56:54,702
-What?
-What?

805
00:56:55,620 --> 00:56:57,747
-What?
-What?

806
00:56:58,540 --> 00:56:59,749
What's wrong with him?

807
00:57:02,877 --> 00:57:05,046
It's dissociative amnesia.

808
00:57:05,130 --> 00:57:07,090
He's mentally shocked.

809
00:57:07,173 --> 00:57:10,051
It looks like a whole part
of his memory has been erased.

810
00:57:10,635 --> 00:57:13,012
We'll need to wait and see
if his memory returns.

811
00:57:15,014 --> 00:57:17,142
Let's wait and see.

812
00:57:17,225 --> 00:57:18,518
What do you mean?

813
00:57:19,477 --> 00:57:21,563
You expect me to believe that?

814
00:57:21,646 --> 00:57:24,566
You saw how fine he was.

815
00:57:24,649 --> 00:57:26,734
What? Wait, Doctor!

816
00:57:26,818 --> 00:57:29,404
Shouldn't we do an MRI scan again?

817
00:57:29,487 --> 00:57:30,447
Hey.

818
00:57:31,072 --> 00:57:34,200
It's possible to temporarily lose
some memory when you're in shock.

819
00:57:34,284 --> 00:57:37,245
No, that's not possible.
That can't happen.

820
00:57:37,328 --> 00:57:40,999
We can't catch those jerks
if he doesn't remember!

821
00:57:47,797 --> 00:57:49,716
YU DONG-MAN

822
00:57:57,390 --> 00:58:00,518
PROFESSOR'S OFFICE

823
00:58:20,371 --> 00:58:22,832
HERE'S THE VIDEO ANALYSIS RESULT

824
00:58:29,005 --> 00:58:30,256
It's 4178.

825
00:58:30,340 --> 00:58:31,299
What?

826
00:58:31,382 --> 00:58:32,842
Wait a minute.

827
00:58:32,926 --> 00:58:35,637
Wait. Hold on!

828
00:58:35,720 --> 00:58:37,180
Professor Yu!

829
00:58:37,263 --> 00:58:39,724
-Excuse me!
-Professor Yu!

830
00:58:39,807 --> 00:58:41,601
Stop right there! Wait!

831
00:58:41,684 --> 00:58:43,478
-Hey!
-Professor Yu!

832
00:58:48,650 --> 00:58:50,527
Stop right there! Hey!

833
00:58:51,110 --> 00:58:51,945
Stop!

834
00:58:53,029 --> 00:58:55,365
KOREAN NATIONAL POLICE UNIVERSITY

835
00:58:55,448 --> 00:58:57,075
Hey, you punk!

836
00:58:57,659 --> 00:58:58,743
Professor Yu!

837
00:58:59,827 --> 00:59:01,162
I said, stop!

838
00:59:01,246 --> 00:59:03,456
It's a gray sedan.

839
00:59:04,791 --> 00:59:06,960
When it rains, the truck gets messy.

840
00:59:10,255 --> 00:59:13,633
This is the last piece of advice
I can give politely to a loser like you.

841
00:59:14,259 --> 00:59:15,885
Leave without causing any trouble.

842
00:59:17,303 --> 00:59:18,513
Wait!

843
00:59:26,980 --> 00:59:29,315
Hey! Darn it…

844
00:59:32,277 --> 00:59:34,988
What? What are you doing here?

845
00:59:36,114 --> 00:59:38,116
You asked for my help.

846
00:59:39,325 --> 00:59:40,660
Do you still need my help?

847
00:59:41,619 --> 00:59:42,996
What did you say, you punk?

848
00:59:44,163 --> 00:59:47,875
You asked me to help you
catch those jerks.

849
00:59:47,959 --> 00:59:49,210
Do you still need my help?

850
00:59:53,423 --> 00:59:54,966
I feel like I can

851
00:59:56,175 --> 00:59:57,468
protect those who are hurt

852
00:59:58,428 --> 01:00:01,014
and catch the bad guys when I'm with you.

853
01:00:03,016 --> 01:00:06,644
A way to protect my people.

854
01:00:07,770 --> 01:00:09,689
The right way to protect them.

855
01:00:09,772 --> 01:00:13,234
Not as Hacker Yoon,
but as a student of this school.

856
01:00:14,611 --> 01:00:16,195
Can I find the right way

857
01:00:17,071 --> 01:00:18,656
as I work with you?

858
01:00:56,444 --> 01:00:59,489
This is all the material I collected
while chasing the illegal gambling ring.

859
01:00:59,572 --> 01:01:00,740
I'll come back in a month.

860
01:01:00,823 --> 01:01:03,034
These are the culprit's footprints.
They're 285mm.

861
01:01:03,117 --> 01:01:04,786
Could it be Professor Kwon Hyuk-phil?

862
01:01:04,869 --> 01:01:07,497
I can feel the stare.
Hands are faster than eyes.

863
01:01:07,580 --> 01:01:09,082
-I saw everything.
-Since when?

864
01:01:09,165 --> 01:01:10,833
Since the moment you inserted that wire.

865
01:01:10,917 --> 01:01:12,251
That sly punk.

866
01:01:12,335 --> 01:01:14,128
Let's go. I'm going
to catch him no matter what.

867
01:01:14,212 --> 01:01:17,090
What was that?
You look like you saw a puppy.

868
01:01:17,173 --> 01:01:19,258
If he looks cute to you,
then you're already into him.

869
01:01:19,342 --> 01:01:21,844
Hey! Don't make that toothy smile.

870
01:01:21,928 --> 01:01:25,014
If a student here makes
physical contact to show sexual desire,

871
01:01:25,098 --> 01:01:27,975
they will be expelled instantly.

872
01:01:28,059 --> 01:01:29,852
Oh Kang-hui, you're expelled!

